reviews.review_text: i can remember this night like it was yesterday.  bob dylan opened up.

My last show - THANK YOU FOR A REAL GOOD TIME This show will always have a special place in my heart. I remember Jerry looking exhausted but still up there giving it his best shot.Some of my favorites were played that night, Same Thing - China > Rider and a nice Spanish Jam.You know the writing was on the wall for years but who would have known that in less than 3 months the big guy would be gone. I miss Jerry very much to this day and treasure this show as well as the 300 others I saw between 1978 to 1995.SUCH A LONG LONG TIME TO BE GONE AND A SHORT TIME TO BE THERE.

listened under http://www.archive.org/details/gd86-04-21.sbd.jeffm.1857.sbeok.shnf


Reviewer: lobster12 -   - October 17, 2005 

Subject: no big deal My 2 cents, the worst performance of a GD song was Wharf rat at NJ 95.

last Jerry show for me....... Although it wasn't a stellar show, it was still the Dead and I will have to say, there is NOTHING like a Grateful Dead concert! I still carry the ticket stub for this show with me today! Thank you Jerry. I love you as much today as I did then, even more! ♥

Final GD show At the time I thought this was head and shoulders above Highgate (not saying much).  I didn't think the music was to bad until Wharf Rat and then it was painfully obvious something was wrong.  I rode down to NJ from Maine on a WTOS concert caravan and remember an older head telling us to "see as many shows as you can because Jerry is not doing well at all" Truer words have never been spoken. 3* because I was there.
One and only show! I was 14 at this show! So glad I made it to one. Thanks so much Tapers for letting me relive this enormous moment in my life!
I was there For as rough as Jerry played that summer..this show stood out to me. I went to 7 that summer. Love this show!

Not Half Bad for 95 We're literally weeks away from the end at this point. 

I was 16, at my 3rd and final show, and there with my brother and my dad. It's been 30 years since I've listened to this show and I'm going through it now. 

Setlist is great, playing isn't bad, and the energy is there. I wish there was a soundboard, but this AUD holds up
